{"type":"message","id":"1f58cb3c","parentId":"9e4154de","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:41:36.726Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-04-03 13:41 GMT-3] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Find and validate a working native primitive for real supervisor -> operator invocation in the current OpenClaw environment, without assuming ACP as central. Goal: make `sm_s3_visual_planning` able to launch at least one real operator successfully without degraded fallback, if possible. Investigate viable mechanisms (e.g. openclaw agent CLI, sessions_spawn mode:run, sessions_send, other documented native paths), compare against current environment constraints, and test the most promising path. Also fix/register b2_director if straightforward and relevant, but priority is supervisor->operator real invocation. Work in C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2 and related agent/runtime config as needed. Edit files/scripts/docs if useful. At the end report: chosen primitive, what was proven, blockers remaining, whether degraded fallback is eliminated."}],"timestamp":1775234496711}}
