{"type":"message","id":"a76d8cd9","parentId":"f369ff6d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:42:18.969Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_39q0hMvV3xNbg9S7t7roaaxc|fc_05ec0761a6007d8f0169cfede0c9d8819182653ab9a6654dd4","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command still running (session quick-canyon, pid 53360). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"quick-canyon","pid":53360,"startedAt":1775234528934,"cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","tail":"claw-nerve\\docs\\DEPLOYMENT-C.md:105:     \"allow\": [\"cron\", \"gateway\", \"sessions_spawn\"]\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-nerve\\docs\\INSTALL.md:54: - adding required gateway tool allow entries such as `cron`, `gateway`, and `sessions_spawn`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-nerve\\docs\\INSTALLER-STEPS.md:283: 3. **Tools allow** - adds `\"cron\"`, `\"gateway\"`, and `\"sessions_spawn\"` to `gateway.tools.allow` in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` (required for OpenClaw =2026.2.23, which denies these tools on `/tools/invoke` by default; `sessions_spawn` is required for Kanban task execution)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-nerve\\docs\\TROUBLESHOOTING.md:263: [\"cron\", \"gateway\", \"sessions_spawn\"]\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-nerve\\docs\\TROUBLESHOOTING.md:457: **Cause:** Nerve requested a child session, but the gateway never surfaced a matching worker session before the timeout. Depending on the path, that usually means the selected root session could not launch the child, the normal `sessions_spawn` path failed, or the child session metadata never became visible to Nerve's poller.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-nerve\\docs\\TROUBLESHOOTING.md:462: - Inspect gateway logs for `sessions.create`, `sessions.send`, or `sessions_spawn` failures\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-nerve\\docs\\TROUBLESHOOTING.md:471: - **Unassigned or `operator` tasks** use the normal `sessions_spawn` path.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-nerve\\docs\\TROUBLESHOOTING.md:473: That means failures can come from a missing assignee root, a child-session create/send failure, the normal `sessions_spawn` path, or a stalled completion poller. On macOS, unassigned or `operator` tasks are rejected outright and must be assigned to a live worker root first.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-nerve\\docs\\TROUBLESHOOTING.md:477: - If the task is unassigned, verify the normal `sessions_spawn` path is working\r\n"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775234538961}}
